picoctf ABSOLUTE NANO writeup

1.connect it and find there is a flag.txt but we cannot use "cat" or other command to print it out

2.use "sudo -l" to check which commands we can use with root user

3.after using previous command , we know that we can use /bin/nano in /etc/sudoers with root

4.so we use "sudo /bin/nano /etc/sudoers"

5.and press "ctrl r" in sudoers , input which file you want to read it 

6.absolutely , we input flag.txt

7.get flag!
